title: "Semantic Drift: A Novel Reliability Challenge in MCP Tool Descriptions"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-06-29
url: "https://github.com/Mukkandi-Sridhar/SemanticDrift"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Mukkandi-Sridhar/SemanticDrift"
abstract: >
  This repository contains the research proposal and pilot study introducing "Semantic Drift", a phenomenon where an LLM's understanding of a tool's purpose diverges from the developer's intent due to contextual variations, prompting nuances, or descriptive ambiguity within the Model Context Protocol (MCP).
